p align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/02 4:07:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3412.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> ddubois: <i> I agree that it is a waste of our time to argue if you are going to adamantly ignore any presented logic</i><br>
<br>
Do you not ignore the logic I present?<br>
<br>
Say for example if you have an Infiltrator that deals 25% more overall melee damage than a Shadowblade. Through the Left Axe improved Scaling, it now scales appropriately like that of an Infiltrator using a slash style.<br>
<br>
In this snapshot of combat without styles:<br>
<br>
Infiltrator deals 125 damage<br>
Shadowblade deals 100 damage<br>
<br>
<b>In this example, Infiltrators are 25% more damaging.</b><br>
<br>
In this snapshot of combat with styles:<br>
<br>
Infiltrator deals 125 + 75 damage (1 weapon's slash style)<br>
Shadowblade deals 100 + 75 damage (1 weapon's LA style)<br>
<br>
<b>In this example, Infiltrators are 14.3% more damaging.</b><br>
<br>
When it comes time for game balance, it is INCORRECT to correct the Shadowblade Left Axe deficiency in terms of what is calculated after styles are accounted for. If that were the case, then 14.3% would be added to the Shadowblade base damage, and in the patched scenario, Infiltrators will still deal 125 base damage, with Shadowblades 114.3 damage.<br>
<br>
It IS correct to analyze the base damage BEFORE styles are applied. The same holds true for Poisons. If you add another +80 damage to both scenarios:<br>
<br>
Infiltrator: 125 base + 75 style + 80 poison = 280<br>
Shadowblade: 100 base + 75 style + 80 poison = 255<br>
<br>
That would mean Infiltrators are only 10% more damaging. If that 10% were added to the base damage of the Shadowblade, it would only yield a 110 damage for the base.<br>
<br>
This is the entire point of keeping styles and poison damage away from balancing the base damage. If you don't break combat down to it's component parts, you are going to get a lot of incorrect numbers that will not balance things out for the better of Shadowblades. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A> at: 6/1/02 4:08:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaiden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aiden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/1/02 5:01:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3412.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> woot,never thought id see elaa arguing for shadowblades. but in all reality its pointless,appreciate it though.<br>
