<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> When it comes time for game balance, it is INCORRECT to correct the Shadowblade Left Axe deficiency in terms of what is calculated after styles are accounted for</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
We'll just have to disagree.  I feel it would be incorrect to attempt to &quot;balance&quot; small facets of individual game mechanics, and not focus on the overall picture.  When you claim that one class does X% more damage, but you are only referring to a small subset of the sources of damage, you are doing a disservice to the players, the developers, and to mathmeticians everwhere.  You are effectively manipulating statistics in order to overstate your case.  And the folks who aren't aware of the subtlety will end up coming away from ther thread thinking &quot;Ella said Infiltrators do 15% more damage than SBs&quot; when you are really talking about what is, for all intents and puposes, a meaningless stastic: &quot;base damage&quot;.<br>
<br>
