<br>
What ddubois said about 37.5% chance offhand weapon used does not equal 37.5% *overall* added damage is a valid point.<br>
<br>
Suppose in an extreme case, some stupid nightshade was holding a piece of paper in his offhand which does 0 (zero) damage... It's easy to see that 1 weapon equals 2 weapons here and therefore the effective damage output is not increased by 37.5%<br>
<br>
The point is: there is a spectrum of combinations of main-hand weapon used and offhand weapon used and you have to find out the distribution of players out there for each specific combination in order to find out the real expected added damage given that a generic player has 37.5% chance to swing his offhand weapon.<br>
<br>
Suppose it is the case that all rogues use 2 identical weapons (and I believe that is the majority class), then your conclusion would hold for exactly 37.5% overall damaged added. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/u13thmonkey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>13thMonkey</A> at: 6/2/02 12:27:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwoopya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woopya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/2/02 4:54:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3412.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /r</span><hr size=1> /reply Elaa<br>
