For the LAST time, TEST TEST TEST! PLZ DO NOT CALCULATE. You so called &quot;snapshots&quot; are not actual snapshots they are calculations. Here is yet another reason your calculator lies:<br>
<br>
You assume base dmg + style bonus = total damage. This is what you claim in your snapshots. This is ONLY true for 1 attack and not at all true for the entire fight. Base dmg for cd/dw users IS greatly effected by the haste cap at high levels. On the other hand, dw/cd users style attacks ALWAYS attack at the speed of the mainhand weapon. So there is a potential HUGE variation in the speed between style attacks and non style attacks(base dmg).   So your calculations hold true for 1 attack, but do NOT include any effects of the speed of attacks, and are therefor way off when forcasted out over time.   <br>
<br>
BTW why would this be off topic? The fixes to sbs in your original post are based on your numbers if im not mistaken. I am pointing out mistakes you have made, like assuming 37.5% offhand swing rate = 37.5% more dmg, like assuming base dmg +style bonus dmg = total dmg for an entire fight, like the complete ommision of the effects of the haste cap(only greatly effects cd/dw users) etc, etc, etc...How is challenging the numbers you draw your conclusions from off topic? <br>
<br>
YES inf's do more dmg than SBs. YES SBs (and NS) need to be braught in line. However, your numbers are wrong and balancing them according to calculations that are a)not tested and b)not correct will only lead to another type of imbalance. <br>
